  "prompt": "I didn't kiss on the first date, is this bad and what should I do from this point on?",
  "response": "Not kissing on the first date is completely normal and should not be seen as a negative thing. Here are some suggestions:\n\n1. If you like the person:\n- Continue communicating\n- Plan another date\n- Be yourself and let things progress naturally\n- Show continued interest through texts/calls\n\n2. If you're interested but hesitant:\n- Wait until you feel more comfortable\n- Don't rush physical intimacy\n- Focus on getting to know each other\n\n3. If they seem disappointed:\n- Be confident in your decision\n- Explain that you prefer taking things slow\n- Most mature people will respect your boundaries\n\n4. General advice:\n- Trust your instincts\n- Only do what feels right for you\n- Communication is key\n\nRemember, everyone moves at a different pace in relationships, and there's no universal \"right\" timeline for physical intimacy.\n\nWould you like to discuss this further or share more context about your specific situation?",
